1
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:05,900
I'll get home early tomorrow.
Last Episode

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,500
I will call Auntie, too.

3
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:13,500
Alright.

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:18,000
Then Uncle, please tell her for me. Yes.

5
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,700
What is it?

6
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,300
Aunt and Uncle had a little quarrel.

7
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:35,200
Why Uncle let me play the timpani instead of a pretty instrument.

8
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,900
I was curious, too. Why timpani?

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,700
It's a difficult instrument to approach.

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:49,700
At first, I started with a small drum.

11
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:53,100
I went to see a a drum and fife band with Uncle, and I was enchanted.

12
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:57,700
The drum sound felt like it was coming from another world.

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,900
What about you, Yun?

14
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,000
The piano?

15
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,700
My mother played the piano, that was why.

16
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:12,000
I heard it from when I was in the womb.

17
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:17,500
So who was tone-deaf, your mother or your father?

18
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:21,200
I don't know, I haven't heard them sing.

19
00:01:21,210 --> 00:01:23,970
I guess it was probably Father.

20
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:25,750
Father?

21
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:28,610
I think you're right.

22
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:32,010
Then,

23
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:35,700
if you want, I will fix it for you.

24
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:38,460
Yi Yeong's clinic for the tone deaf.-

25
00:01:38,460 --> 00:01:43,780
For ten minutes, I'll give you good deal, 10,000 won (about $ 8).

26
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:53,190
Alright, follow me.

27
00:01:53,190 --> 00:01:57,400
♪ On that exciting day

28
00:01:57,400 --> 00:02:03,070
♪ On that day, beautiful day

29
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,610
Now.

30
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:08,560
Come on.

31
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:14,290
♪ On that exciting  day

32
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:20,990
♪ On that day, beautiful day

33
00:02:23,770 --> 00:02:26,920
How can I begin to fix this?

34
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:31,990
First of all, "day~" take care of that wavering.

35
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:35,910
♪ On that exciting  day

36
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:40,860
♪ On that day, beautiful day

37
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:47,360
♪ On that exciting day

38
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,240
♪ On that day
- You're doing well, like that.

39
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:53,970
♪ beautiful day

40
00:02:54,660 --> 00:02:55,840
You're doing well.

41
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,680
Now, ♪ my heart flutters so much

42
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:05,420
♪ my heart flutters ... flutters so much

43
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:09,020
♪ my heart flutters so much

44
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:15,580
♪ it keeps beating

45
00:03:15,580 --> 00:03:18,000
♫ beautiful day ♫

46
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:25,780
♫ my heart flutters so much, my heart flutters so much ♫

47
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:30,260
♫ it keeps beating ♫

48
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:33,870
♫ that brilliant day ♫

49
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:38,760
♫ that day, beautiful day ♫

50
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:45,300
♫ on that happy day, be loving you ♫

51
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,800
♫ to be loving you ♫

52
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:53,660
♫ I'm gonna love with you ♫

53
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:04,950
Please spare me. Please spare me.

54
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:06,540
Yi Yeong?

55
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:08,470
Please spare—

56
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,160
Did you have a bad dream?

57
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,420
Yes.

58
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:22,620
It's the same dream I've had for a year.

59
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:27,610
Since now I'll have you by my side, I guess I won't have that nightmare so often.

60
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:31,580
I'll stay here with you, so sleep comfortably.

61
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:33,380
Yes.

62
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:42,630
I... can we sleep while holding hands?

63
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:44,900
Just holding hands.

64
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,570
It's warm.

65
00:04:58,110 --> 00:05:03,490
We met under some difficult circumstances.

66
00:05:03,490 --> 00:05:08,500
So I hope that we never part

67
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:12,130
and stay together for a long, long time.

68
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:17,560
Until we both get sick of each other.

69
00:05:20,370 --> 00:05:24,360
Hurry and sleep. Don't have bad dreams.

70
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:27,000
Yes.

71
00:05:32,990 --> 00:05:35,770
You have to speak for me to know!

72
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:38,060
I just don't know.

73
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:41,590
I can't remember.

74
00:05:42,780 --> 00:05:44,560
Please spare me, please spare me,

75
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,880
please spare me.

76
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:52,330
Do you remember whom you killed?

77
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:58,080
Shall we just date? I think I like you, Yun.

78
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:01,550
It might have been you who stabbed Ian.

79
00:06:01,550 --> 00:06:05,900
You may not remember, but you were someone that my brother loved.

80
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,820
I don't know anything, I told you I don't remember.

81
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:09,950
Someone died.

82
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:12,550
All the bones in his body were broken, and his intestines ruptured...

83
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:14,380
Please stop!

84
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:16,710
Even if you don't want to remember, please remember.

85
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,740
I will make an effort.

86
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:22,670
I will take responsibility for everything.

87
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:26,240
Since I may have been the one who killed your brother.

88
00:06:27,350 --> 00:06:29,680
Yun, you don't care what happens to me, do you?

89
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:32,820
Even if I disappeared, you wouldn't care, would you?

90
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:42,470
All the times we spent together were all lies, after all.

91
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,570
Yes.

92
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,910
I understand.

93
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,690
What is it?

94
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,760
How surprising. When did you get here?

95
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:26,600
Just now. I had an early morning consultation.

96
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:30,320
You are smiling from ear-to-ear. Was camping fun?

97
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,590
Yes.

98
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:35,410
Well, it's always fun to be outdoors and have a good time.

99
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,580
Yi Yeong,

100
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:44,350
the truth is that there was something I wasn't able to tell you before.

101
00:07:44,350 --> 00:07:48,640
To me? What is it?

102
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:59,680
Do you remember this diary?

103
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:03,770
It was in your bag on the day of the accident.

104
00:08:04,540 --> 00:08:06,420
You said you threw that away.

105
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:08,760
I kept it.

106
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:13,220
But why didn't you tell me? This isn't such a big deal.

107
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:28,340
There was some reason you couldn't tell me, huh?

108
00:08:29,370 --> 00:08:35,660
The truth is, I knew Jang Yun from before.

109
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:40,460
I couldn't tell you because I thought you shouldn't know about that.

110
00:08:40,460 --> 00:08:43,620
Jang Yun's brother died from that accident.

111
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:48,880
I was afraid it would make things even more difficult for you, so out of desperation, I hid it.

112
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:55,380
I don't understand what you are saying at all.

113
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:59,120
You thought it would make things more difficult for me?

114
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:13,020
What is that?

115
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,900
Why is Yun's photo in there?

116
00:09:24,850 --> 00:09:27,400
These came out well.

117
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,780
Oh, this man—

118
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,220
♫ the whole wide world to me♫

119
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,950
Who?

120
00:09:36,970 --> 00:09:37,750
♫ Darling you ♫

121
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:41,170
Jang Do Hun, right?

122
00:09:41,170 --> 00:09:43,290
How do you know my hyung?

123
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:46,590
Hyung? He's your older brother?

124
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:49,770
Yes, my hyung.

125
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:54,620
♫ Darling you mean the whole wide world♫

126
00:09:54,620 --> 00:10:00,960
He was a teaching assistant I had a huge crush on during college.

127
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:04,000
You liked my hyung?

128
00:10:05,970 --> 00:10:08,310
One-sided crush.

129
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:11,810
He disappeared suddenly, so I wondered where he went.

130
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:15,830
Where is he now?

131
00:10:15,830 --> 00:10:20,080
He's not here, he's studying in the U.S.

132
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:24,120
Is that right? How nice for him.

133
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:27,390
Can I have this? It's such a nice memento.

134
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,790
Sure, whatever.

135
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:32,760
Thanks.

136
00:10:39,140 --> 00:10:43,170
Jang Do Hun

137
00:10:46,410 --> 00:10:50,750
Jang Do Hun

138
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:56,460
I think Jang Yun is going to the U.S. today.

139
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,000
What?

140
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,410
Yi Yeong.

141
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:14,510
I will store your things and continue to pay rent on your place.

142
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:16,190
If you want me to get rid of it, let me know.

143
00:11:16,190 --> 00:11:18,450
You can decide on your own.

144
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:24,890
What about Hong Yi Yeong? Is it alright to just leave like this?

145
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:28,640
I can't be responsible for that.

146
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,850
I know. Let's go.

147
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:52,100
Yun?

148
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:54,590
Yun?

149
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:57,070
Yun!?

150
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:08,350
To Yi Yeong

151
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:13,660
I'm sorry to leave a letter like this to you.

152
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:16,980
I don't think I can say this looking at your face.

153
00:12:17,890 --> 00:12:22,810
I wanted to tell you, but I just couldn't find the words.

154
00:12:22,810 --> 00:12:24,780
No.

155
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:31,750
I thought about everything that's happened.

156
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:35,930
I really gave you such a hard time.

157
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:40,180
I made you remember things you did not have to.

158
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:44,920
And made you suffer things you did not have to.

159
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:52,380
All the times we spent together were difficult and full of suffering.

160
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:56,590
And I'm so sorry.

161
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:02,180
Yun!

162
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:04,920
Yun!

163
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,270
Yun!

164
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:14,840
I hope that your future is only full of happiness.

165
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:17,590
♫ I regret ♫

166
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:20,590
♫ that I couldn't hold on to you ♫

167
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:23,410
If you do that for me, I think I can endure,

168
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:28,310
even though I will be far away from you.

169
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:32,000
♫ in the memory spent with you ♫

170
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:37,480
♫ Just the longing is left in that place ♫

171
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:40,880
♫ When time passes will it get better? ♫

172
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:44,170
The exam time will be from now until 12 p.m.

173
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:47,780
Once you are finished, please leave your answer sheet on your desk and leave the classroom quietly.

174
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:52,360
He was a teaching assistant that I had a huge crush on in college.

175
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:57,200
You liked my hyung?

176
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,770
One-sided crush.

177
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:03,600
So what is your real name?

178
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,350
Jang Do Hun.

179
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:10,650
♫ On the days I long and long again for you ♫

180
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:14,980
♫ in the memory spent with you ♫

181
00:14:14,980 --> 00:14:20,470
♫ Just the longing is left in that place ♫

182
00:14:20,470 --> 00:14:28,620
IAN Art Center
One Year Later

183
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:31,740
Hello.

184
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:33,880
Hello.

185
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,520
Hello.

186
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,620
Hello.

187
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:44,500
Congratulations on your promotion, Manager.

188
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,850
Thank you.

189
00:14:58,950 --> 00:15:00,890
Jang Yun
Piano Recital

190
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:04,570
Pianist Jang Yun Homecoming Solo Recital

191
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:11,980
President Yun Mi Rae

192
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:14,790
You got a bit of a tan on your face?

193
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:20,930
Is that so? I spend a lot of time outdoors lately.

194
00:15:20,930 --> 00:15:24,500
I asked you here because I had a request.

195
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,530
And I missed seeing you, too.

196
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:28,060
What is your request?

197
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:33,470
I was hoping you can be a guest performer at our symphony's one-year anniversary concert.

198
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:38,390
I'm sure there may be some opposition, but I can persuade the board.

199
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:39,510
How about it?

200
00:15:39,510 --> 00:15:43,520
I'm sorry, I'm conducting at a different orchestra these days.

201
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:47,330
Is that right? Why not let me know?

202
00:15:47,330 --> 00:15:48,430
Where is it?

203
00:15:48,430 --> 00:15:51,400
It's a youth orchestra in Chuncheon.

204
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:55,370
It's a small orchestra, made of kids who can't attend music lessons after school.

205
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:58,350
It’s a youth orchestra.

206
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:01,320
So you're teaching children?

207
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:05,440
Actually, I had something to ask you too.

208
00:16:06,130 --> 00:16:08,570
Let's form a relationship with your orchestra and mine.

209
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:12,100
The orchestra members would travel and teach my kids twice a year.

210
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:16,600
And when you change musical instruments, please donate the used ones to us.

211
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,380
This sort of proposal...

212
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,690
I absolutely accept, of course.

213
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:31,370
Thank you...

214
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:12,880
Ha Eun Ju went independent, so why is she a guest performer?

215
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:18,900
The President personally invited her to perform at our anniversary concert.

216
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:21,180
What loyalty.

217
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:25,730
Loyalty, my foot. I'm sure she's coming because they paid her well.

218
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:34,490
Did you see the bulletin board? Jang Yun is putting on a solo recital.

219
00:17:36,170 --> 00:17:38,620
He didn't contact you?

220
00:17:39,530 --> 00:17:41,060
- No.
- Aish,

221
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,190
what a jerk.

222
00:18:48,690 --> 00:18:54,320
♪ Eggs are only good if you put it in ramyun when it's almost cooked...

223
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,590
You don’t know much about life.

224
00:18:56,590 --> 00:19:00,220
Yi Yeong, were you the kimchi type?

225
00:19:00,220 --> 00:19:03,260
Let me treat you today. Fried rice.

226
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:26,150
Here's a fried ham and cheese rice and fried kimchi rice.

227
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:31,340
Please don't speak to me.

228
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:47,000
But I waited here for so long, I had no idea when you would come.

229
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,230
Why would you wait for me? Don't you have a phone?

230
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:54,870
You changed your number, though. Did you change it because you didn't want to see me?

231
00:19:54,870 --> 00:19:58,380
If you don't have my number, you can't call me?

232
00:19:58,380 --> 00:20:02,010
Ah, you didn't have a number yourself, you ditched it when you ran away.

233
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:07,780
Of course, that was because if I heard your voice,

234
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:11,600
I didn't think I could leave.

235
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:16,410
Are you making fun of me? I'm just a joke to you, then and now.

236
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:21,600
Did you think I would be moved if you appeared like this? Should I be crying tears of joy?

237
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,590
No.

238
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:26,520
You ran away without saying a single word. No contact for a whole year.

239
00:20:26,520 --> 00:20:28,570
So why did you come here?

240
00:20:28,570 --> 00:20:29,680
I came to see you, Yi Yeong.

241
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:33,260
But you ran away, saying you are sorry or whatever.

242
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,630
I'm sorry.

243
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:42,920
How selfish. You leave when you want to

244
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,960
and then say you miss me? Is that enough?

245
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:48,740
You say "sorry," and is that enough?

246
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:06,770
Don't follow me, it's quite unpleasant.

247
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:11,120
I'm not trying to make you feel unpleasant, my home is that way.

248
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,790
What?

249
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:16,160
My hyung kept the room, and now I moved back in.

250
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:19,110
- When?
- This afternoon.

251
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:24,690
I heard you passed the audition. Now you're an official orchestra member?

252
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:31,460
Yes. I am the one and only timpanist for our symphony. Why?

253
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:33,530
I'm proud of you.

254
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:44,390
To commemorate my move back here, how about a part-time job?

255
00:21:44,390 --> 00:21:47,870
- Part-time job?
- Clinic for the tone-deaf?

256
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:51,630
10,000 won for ten minutes. Weekly payment in advance. The contract stops

257
00:21:51,630 --> 00:21:54,430
by mutual agreement. How about it?

258
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:58,420
Fine, let's do it. Sure.

259
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:00,130
Let's do it, okay?

260
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:02,340
Yes, let's do it.

261
00:22:06,870 --> 00:22:08,740
Jang Do Hun.

262
00:22:09,970 --> 00:22:11,800
